ct/panama-francis-interviewed-michael-woods-los-angeles-california-september-1-1995"}, {"speaker": "Teddy Wilson", "relation": "in music group with", "confidence": 1.0, "evidence": "he picked up me and my brother, Gus, and Roy Eldridge from Detroit... So the Speed Webb band had Jonesey on one trumpet, Roy Eldridge on the other... and Roy and Vic and I", "doc_title": "66600_Teddy Wilson oral history interview", "collection": "rutgers", "url": "https://rucore.libraries.rutgers.edu/rutgers-lib/66600/"}, {"speaker": "Greg Thomas", "relation": "knows of", "confidence": 1.0, "evidence": "you need to have Louis Armstrong, Roy Eldridge, Dizzy, and there’s all kind of people... who are great players in their own right who you need to know.", "doc_title": "Greg Thomas interviewed by Monk Rowe, Clinton, New York, October 11, 2014", "collection": "hamilton", "url": "https://litsdigital.hamilton.edu/collections/object/greg-thomas-interviewed-monk-rowe-clinton-new-york-october-11-2014"}, {"speaker": "Cliff Leeman", "relation": "knows of", "confidence": 1.0, "evidence": "I don't think he ever reached the epitome in life that he might have... he also loved Little Jazz Roy Eldridge", "doc_title": "68087_Cliff Leeman oral history interview", "collection": "rutgers", "url": "https://rucore.libraries.rutgers.edu/rutgers-lib/68087/"}, {"speaker": "Trummy Young", "relation": "played with", "confidence": 1.0, "evidence": "At that time I was playing with Roy Eldridge out at Billy Berg's. Me, Roy Eldridge -- Roy had the group", "doc_title": "52300_Trummy Young oral history interview", "collection": "rutgers", "url": "https://rucore.libraries.rutgers.edu/rutgers-lib/52300/"}, {"speaker": "Big Chielf Moore", "relation": "knows of", "confidence": 1.0, "evidence": "No mention of the interviewee (Big Chief Moore) in relation to Roy Eldridge in the provided transcript.", "doc_title": "67259_Big Chief Moore oral history interview", "collection": "rutgers", "url": "https://rucore.libraries.rutgers.